Colombian Stocks: Enka, Fabricato, Grupo Aval Increase

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-03-03T21:24:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/colombian-stocks-enka-fabricato-grupo-aval-increase.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index increased 1.3 percent to 15,334.59, while
the Colcap Index gained 1.3 percent to 1,782.06.  Exporters rose after the U.S. said it is working to move  Colombia ’s trade pact agreement to Congress “as quickly as
possible,” and the lack of a pact “could leave U.S. exporters
to these markets at a competitive disadvantage,” according to
the 2011 trade agenda released on the Office of the U.S. Trade
Representative’s website.    Textiles Fabricato Tejicondor SA (FABRI)   surged 12
percent to 36.3 pesos, the highest level since May 2008.    Enka de Colombia SA (ENKA)  , another textiles producer,
gained 6.9 percent to 15.4 pesos.    Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores (AVAL)  SA advanced 1
percent to 1,585 pesos. The country’s biggest financial holding
company proposed a dividend increase of 6.6 percent to 19.5
pesos per share, according to a report e-mailed by Bogota-based
brokerage Correval SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  